headline: Why Molina Healthcare (MOH) Stock Is Falling Today
summary: Shares of healthcare insurance company Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) fell 6.7% in the morning session after the company reported weak first-quarter 2025 results, missing analysts' expectations on EBITDA despite beating on revenue, EPS, and membership growth. Medical costs ticked up as expected, and EBITDA performance was softer than anticipated.
